		<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_4632577_comm_19339"></div><p>I just read Steele&#8217;s post.on Cashman&#8217;s site, what a fucking joke but this line really stuck out: &#8220;This week alone two arrest warrants were issued for pirates who refused to show up for court, and we are starting to get verdicts against people.&#8221;  Federal arrest warrant for failure to appear in a civil case? I call flat-out BULLSHIT.  You CANNOT be arrested for failing to comply with a summons in a civil case.  Hell, you can&#8217;t even be arrested if you don&#8217;t pay them a dime for a judgment in a civil case.  Even if you could be arrested, federal law enforcement has better shit to do than go hunt down people who failed to comply with a summons for a copyright infringement case.</p>

